Comment: 0,0:21:54.54,0:21:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,ENDING
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.28,0:02:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, come on, can't you work harder?!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:23.83,0:02:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not out strolling around, now!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:25.75,0:02:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you put your back into it more?!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.16,0:02:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Old-timer, you just sit there, quietly! \NWe'll take care of this!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:32.25,0:02:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, now, Gramps, get some rest.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.88,0:02:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like your shoulders rubbed?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:39.68,0:02:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What is this?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:41.01,0:02:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, why are you intentionally building this ship
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.43,0:02:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,up here in the mountains, old-timer?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:45.47,0:02:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Aah... it's because it's not a ship.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.19,0:02:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't a ship?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:50.48,0:02:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, look! \NIf this isn't a ship, then exactly what is it?!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.44,0:02:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It is my... coffin.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.49,0:03:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Coffin?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.95,0:03:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That means, this will be my grave.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.16,0:03:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So this is your grave, old goat man.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.79,0:03:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't pray over it! You'll doom him!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:09.50,0:03:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still too early for this!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.29,0:03:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're over-preparing!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.00,0:03:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Could Gramps be aware that his life is almost over?{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.13,0:03:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you so startled at?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.01,0:03:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Living on an island like this,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.93,0:03:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not unusual that I would \Nmake my own grave, is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:26.22,0:03:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I am going to die someday, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.18,0:03:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Not just "someday," it's going to be really soon.{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.02,0:03:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not unusual for a grave to \Nbe up in the mountains, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.65,0:03:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But why have your grave be a pirate ship?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.86,0:03:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Old man!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.37,0:03:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Wait, old man!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:46.70,0:03:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,C-Coffin, or g-grave, or whatever you call it,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:49.04,0:03:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it's almost finished! \NDon't go jumping the gun!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.62,0:03:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't die yet!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.79,0:03:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Shh... He's just sleeping.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.47,0:04:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you've found the \NStraw Hat pirates, have you?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.30,0:04:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir! \NI believe they have landed on a deserted island,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.14,0:04:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as I reported earlier.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.44,0:04:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, ready to attack at once!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:15.02,0:04:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll storm the island with all of our forces,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.40,0:04:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring down the Straw Hat pirates! \NEvery last one of them!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.19,0:04:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, wait, Captain!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:23.57,0:04:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to those guys with Devil Fruit abilities,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.87,0:04:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll be facing the master swordsman, Roronoa Zoro.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:31.66,0:04:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So what if we are? \NAre you losing your nerve, Sergeant Minchy?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.54,0:04:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not. \NI just want to avoid any unnecessary casualties.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:40.00,0:04:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what would you have us do?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:42.05,0:04:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do as I say, Captain, then you will achieve
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.59,0:04:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,a complete victory with only a few casualties.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.02,0:04:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.69,0:04:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how it's gonna be, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.32,0:05:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yum! How did you make this cheese?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.61,0:05:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,From the island goats' milk. \NIt will give you lots of energy, old-timer.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.70,0:05:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Though at this point, it'll be just a drop in the bucket.{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.58,0:05:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Gramps, it's your turn.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.75,0:05:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... There, checkmate. That's the game.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.34,0:05:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.67,0:05:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No waiting allowed, Nami-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.30,0:05:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You got me. In return, play me again?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.26,0:05:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Nothing beats playing \Nchess against a beauty like you,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.10,0:05:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,while getting my shoulders rubbed!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.31,0:05:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We took in a great catch today!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.52,0:05:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanji, make the old goat man \Nsomething yummy again, would you?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.48,0:05:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm on it.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:44.53,0:05:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Old man, if there's anything else \Nyou want to eat, or have us do,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.11,0:05:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,don't be afraid to speak up, okay? \NWe'll do whatever we can!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.33,0:05:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, I can die happy now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.12,0:05:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in paradise... paradise...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:59.08,0:06:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say that!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.92,0:06:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if the way ahead is short...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.42,0:06:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,...you've gotta live with a positive view!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:03.84,0:06:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,For as long as you live!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.05,0:06:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, doesn't it seem strange?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.84,0:06:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.93,0:06:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The old man's only supposed to have three days to live, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:12.97,0:06:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Three days.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.85,0:06:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Only three days to live.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.68,0:06:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just the briefest moment, isn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:20.98,0:06:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed it is. In just the briefest moment, \Nthree days have gone by.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.40,0:06:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.99,0:06:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So then, how is it that he's still alive and kicking?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.07,0:06:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,More than that, he's healthier \Nthan he was before, isn't he?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.70,0:06:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,More cheese.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.75,0:06:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Old-timer, here's today's medicine.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.13,0:06:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure you take it.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.34,0:06:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need that anymore. \NIt makes all the food taste bad, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:46.71,0:06:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There, checkmate!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:49.47,0:06:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Not again!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.72,0:06:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought the old guy wasn't supposed to live
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.14,0:06:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for more than three more days.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.10,0:06:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,From the way he looks, \Nhe seems good for another 30 years.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.48,0:07:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You misdiagnosed him, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.02,0:07:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No. That can't be right.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:02.77,0:07:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, if I did misdiagnose him, \Nthat wouldn't be so bad, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.98,0:07:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the issue here. If this is how it is,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.86,0:07:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,then no matter what anyone else says, \NI'm leaving the island.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.20,0:07:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. This is no place for me to be \Nforever kissing up to that old man.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.91,0:07:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to have some adventures at sea, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.54,0:07:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, that settles it.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.92,0:07:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Nami, we're setting sail!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.33,0:07:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,C-Can you wait a little while longer?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.38,0:07:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How long are you gonna goof around? \NQuit playing chess, already.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.38,0:07:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I {\i1}can't{\i0} quit playing! I've lost so many times,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.80,0:07:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I ended up pawning the ship to Gramps here.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.22,0:07:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:37.68,0:07:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What are pirates who have lost \Ntheir ship supposed to do?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.14,0:07:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get it back for sure, just wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.73,0:07:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Checkmate.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.32,0:07:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop, already!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:47.57,0:07:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Earthquake!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.15,0:07:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you keep this up, there's no \Ntelling what else will be signed away!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.91,0:07:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want your ship back,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.74,0:07:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll just have to work here on \Nthe island for as much as it's worth.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.00,0:08:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,By my reckoning, in total, \Nyou'll have to work for ten years.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:04.33,0:08:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How's tricks with you?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.71,0:08:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,– Nami-{\i1}san{\i0}! \N– Nami!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.80,0:08:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I thought that if I got lucky,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.14,0:08:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I could get Gramps to tell us where his treasure is.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.76,0:08:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you still going on about that?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.81,0:08:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, we'll have to leave \Nthe old man, and run away.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:23.48,0:08:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,– That's all there is to it. \N– Not me.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:25.44,0:08:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about, Luffy?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.31,0:08:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good thing for us that \NZoro noticed it, or we might have
Dialogue: 10,0:08:30.44,0:08:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,spent the rest of our lives on this \Nisland working for that old man!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.11,0:08:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you figure it out, too?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:35.74,0:08:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't have any adventures around here, Luffy. Let's go.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.45,0:08:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,– Nope. \N– Luffy!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.04,0:08:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A stake is something like a promise, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.46,0:08:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, I don't want to break any promises.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.62,0:08:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is no time to think about appearances!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.88,0:08:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Zoro, what do you say?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.09,0:08:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The captain is the one to decide, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:52.55,0:08:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Luffy!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.62,0:08:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I said no, and I mean no.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:55.34,0:08:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Checkmate.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.93,0:09:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,T-That's...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.60,0:09:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like we {\i1}can{\i0} get the ship back, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:07.94,0:09:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it, Gramps?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.94,0:09:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You got me...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:13.36,0:09:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:14.95,0:09:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We can always count on you, Big Sister!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.87,0:09:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,How's tricks with you?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.83,0:09:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Just fine, thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.62,0:09:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I've lived for many years, \Nbut I've never seen pirates
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.79,0:09:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as interesting as you are. I really like you.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:29.92,0:09:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Big party tonight!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.30,0:09:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, a feast, to celebrate \Nus getting the ship back!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.98,0:09:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Gramps, you're just like a great pirate.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.10,0:09:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can really put it away.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.11,0:09:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Nami-{\i1}chan{\i0}, are you calling me a pirate?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.61,0:09:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you weren't, you wouldn't have \Nsuch first-rate glasses, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.66,0:10:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They are indeed treasure-class, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.91,0:10:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! \NNami, you're trying to get the old man drunk,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:03.87,0:10:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to find out where he keeps his treasure, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:06.25,0:10:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't spell it out for him!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.00,0:10:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Old goat man, do you really have a treasure?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.17,0:10:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I just said, don't go talking so openly!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.01,0:10:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Some things {\i1}do{\i0} have their proper order!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.55,0:10:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,My treasure...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:21.18,0:10:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,...is what I have shared my joys and sorrows with
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.85,0:10:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,ever since washing up on \Nthis island... the island goats.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:28.64,0:10:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What a great story!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:30.69,0:10:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:33.82,0:10:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't just say "gotcha," tell us what you mean!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.78,0:10:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, here's what it means.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.53,0:10:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,For all the great pirates, \Nwho traveled the Grand Line, I am...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:42.49,0:10:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:44.49,0:10:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,...the moneylender who dealt with them.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:47.16,0:10:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Moneylender?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.33,0:10:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. \NI'm Zenny the {\i1}Moneylender{\i0}, not the {\i1}Pirate{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:51.92,0:10:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.71,0:10:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's too bad, huh, Nami?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:54.67,0:10:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, you must have some nerve, \Nlending money to pirates,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.42,0:11:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,don't you, old man?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.13,0:11:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.26,0:11:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, doesn't he? \NDo you think pirates usually borrow money,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.51,0:11:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,then pay it back? Not to mention the interest.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.93,0:11:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. You can bet everyone \Nbilked me out of their debts.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.15,0:11:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Every damn one of those pirates broke their word,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.48,0:11:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and betrayal was second nature to them.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.11,0:11:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So Gramps, it's true that you hate pirates, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.82,0:11:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If I would've just sat back and taken it from them,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:25.37,0:11:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,my business would have been wiped out.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:31.00,0:11:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time I went out to collect on a debt,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.29,0:11:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to fight against pirates,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:36.42,0:11:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,at the risk of my own life.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:42.34,0:11:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a business where you have to be
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.26,0:11:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,stronger than the pirates, isn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:46.43,0:11:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Old goat man, were you that strong?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.02,0:11:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mean to brag, but I was weak. \NBut then, I had a dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.23,0:11:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A dream?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:59.07,0:12:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You did, Gramps?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.09,0:12:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.50,0:12:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay back the money?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.08,0:12:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the man they call Zenny the Moneylender!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.14,0:12:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather see you in hell than \Nhave you run out on your debt.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.02,0:12:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we head to the underworld together?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.10,0:12:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Wait, Zenny! Here!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.65,0:12:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How's tricks? Well, goodbye.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.65,0:12:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no you don't! You give us pirates our due!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:40.32,0:12:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but I am.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.20,0:12:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Zenny! How dare you?!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:51.79,0:12:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Much obliged!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.33,0:12:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I may have been weak, but I had a dream,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.54,0:12:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,so I fought desperately for it. \NNo, I managed to fight for it.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.95,0:13:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Old man, what was your dream?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.55,0:13:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since I was a kid, I wanted to be a pirate.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.80,0:13:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A real pirate. The Pirate King.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.93,0:13:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I first started \Nin the moneylending trade.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.27,0:13:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But instead, I got hit with a sneak \Nattack by some damn pirates,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.02,0:13:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,taking their anger out on me,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.27,0:13:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and I ended up being washed \Nashore for dear life on this island.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:19.98,0:13:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That was 20 years ago now, was it?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.61,0:13:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you been making that grave for 20 years?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:25.95,0:13:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, I planned to build \Nthe ship near the sea,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.62,0:13:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but bringing the lumber down from \Nthe mountain was too much for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.04,0:13:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I didn't give up, no matter what, \Nbut built it up in the mountains.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.62,0:13:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a hell of a dream I couldn't \Ncalculate with my abacus.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.67,0:13:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A hell of an adventure!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.50,0:13:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But somewhere along the way, \Nmy eyes were opened.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.47,0:13:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I knew it, I was too old \Nto set sail for the Grand Line.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.72,0:13:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So much for my dream of being a pirate.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.77,0:13:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams are just dreams, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.48,0:14:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you give up, old goat man?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:06.61,0:14:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Age doesn't have anything to do with it.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.41,0:14:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to become a pirate, \Nthen you should do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.83,0:14:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, now, Luffy,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.24,0:14:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,what are we going to do if the \Nold man takes you seriously?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.91,0:14:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Pirates need a ship,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.50,0:14:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Sanji, give me another.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.83,0:14:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Coming up.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:19.12,0:14:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}and the old man's ship is a coffin in the mountains.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:20.00,0:14:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:22.09,0:14:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So we just have to bring it down, don't we?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.13,0:14:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say it like it's so simple!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:26.47,0:14:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... there's still time...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.84,0:14:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There, you see? \NThe old man is taking you seriously!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.35,0:14:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No he's not. \NYou're just drunk, aren't you, Gramps?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.22,0:14:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm drunk, I'm drunk!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.94,0:14:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he is?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.73,0:14:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This straw-hatted lad has got \Nme absolutely intoxicated!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.57,0:14:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! Here's looking forward to the day
Dialogue: 10,0:14:47.32,0:14:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when the Zenny Pirates set sail!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.91,0:14:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we really do this?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:54.58,0:14:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Lure the Straw Hat pirates off \Nthe island, all by ourselves?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.96,0:15:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how strong they might be,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.04,0:15:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,they're still a bunch of greenhorn kids.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.37,0:15:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Depending on how this is done, \Nwe have nothing to fear from them.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.05,0:15:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not as though I'm going to fight them. \NNow, just watch.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.68,0:15:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the captain going to be able \Nto take the Straw Hat pirates?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:12.72,0:15:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That isn't any of my concern.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.47,0:15:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,While the bigwigs are off fighting for justice,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.85,0:15:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll just be taking away the treasure.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.30,0:15:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Corporal, I'm going to put you to work, as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:22.90,0:15:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I will reward you handsomely.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.94,0:15:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.83,0:15:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Age doesn't have anything to do with it, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.29,0:15:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He went and said something to \Nmake an old man like me dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:44.63,0:15:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That straw-hatted lad is a nefarious boy.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.17,0:15:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,– You're right. \N– Robin-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.72,0:15:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Our captain also rescues people \Nwho want to die, without asking them,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:55.97,0:15:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and lets them live.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.43,0:16:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you glad he let you live?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.31,0:16:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed... I'm not quite sure about that yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:03.27,0:16:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not sorry he did.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.61,0:16:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell by your face. \NRobin-{\i1}chan{\i0}, your life is just getting started.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.28,0:16:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But me... my dream will \Nremain at rest here, forever.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.54,0:16:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.72,0:16:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad news! Everyone, wake up!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.47,0:16:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure slept good. Time for breakfast?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.80,0:16:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The Navy! The Navy is here!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.89,0:16:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.90,0:16:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one ship?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.23,0:16:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't look like they're \Nabout to attack, either.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.98,0:16:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What on earth is it doing here?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.65,0:16:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Straw Hat pirates!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.69,0:16:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Sergeant Minchy, of the Navy. \NIt's a pleasure.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.92,0:16:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A pleasure?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.03,0:16:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I'm terribly sorry about the other day.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:00.37,0:17:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If we had known better \Nwho we were dealing with,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:02.45,0:17:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we wouldn't have chased you around like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.75,0:17:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you accept our apologies.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:06.43,0:17:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Strange, isn't it? \NIt's only natural for the Navy to chase pirates.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.13,0:17:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He's being unusually hospitable. \NWatch yourselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.68,0:17:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,P-Please! Don't get upset! \NI understand that you're the ones
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.30,0:17:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,who defeated Crocodile back in Alabasta, aren't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.27,0:17:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't think of fighting \Nagainst pirates as great as you are!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.35,0:17:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Believe me. I mean, if we meant to attack you,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:29.15,0:17:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,would we come here with only one ship?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.19,0:17:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you know? \NThe guy is afraid of us, isn't he?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.53,0:17:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Even assuming we did risk our lives to fight you,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.03,0:17:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it wouldn't earn us a single penny.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:41.46,0:17:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.33,0:17:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we're just here to investigate the island.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.16,0:17:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a newly discovered island \Nthat doesn't appear on our maps.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.17,0:17:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Investigate? \NThere's just an old man and his island goats here.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.75,0:17:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, \Nwhere did the old guy go?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.76,0:17:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Then Zenny is being \Nsafely cared for here, isn't he?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.59,0:18:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Zenny?{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.97,0:18:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Once our survey is done, \Nwe're planning to return to our base.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.81,0:18:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd best set sail on out \Nof here as soon as you can.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:07.85,0:18:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't blame you.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.27,0:18:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Naval headquarters is in a frenzy \Nto eliminate you guys, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.82,0:18:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's it. \NSounds like this is our chance, as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.24,0:18:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go get the food. \NHave to call Robin down, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.25,0:18:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.17,0:18:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,...a trap! A trap by the Navy!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.30,0:18:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we setting sail, Luffy?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:39.30,0:18:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's good weather past the fog.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.76,0:18:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The waves are gentle, and we won't, \Nby any means, lay a hand on you.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.10,0:18:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, go ahead.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.35,0:18:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I go when I want to! You don't decide when!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:50.90,0:18:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If I were the Navy, \NI'd fight desperately against us,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:53.40,0:18:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,even with only one ship!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.40,0:18:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, something else is strange!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.65,0:19:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you know Gramps' name was Zenny?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.16,0:19:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't say a word about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.53,0:19:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Well, you see...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.08,0:19:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm suspicious of what kind \Nof survey you plan to conduct.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:09.08,0:19:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not, by any chance, \Nafter Gramps' treasure, are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.63,0:19:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it, huh? I don't trust this guy!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.13,0:19:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They've caught on, have they?{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.88,0:19:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}About the mountain of treasure \Nthat Zenny the Moneylender{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.43,0:19:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}had signed over to him to cover the pirates' debts?{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.85,0:19:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it! Gramps {\i1}does{\i0} have a treasure!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:28.93,0:19:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I smell gunpowder.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.53,0:19:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it that bastard's cannons?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.44,0:19:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just one ship's cannons.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:34.48,0:19:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's from more cannons than I can count.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.53,0:19:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that there?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:37.90,0:19:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If we had set sail, we would have been caught
Dialogue: 10,0:19:39.74,0:19:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in a sneak attack by that fleet!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.78,0:19:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Mess with us, will they?! \NI don't care if they are a fleet!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.87,0:19:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,– Come and get me! \N– W-Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.38,0:19:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,L-L-Luffy...!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.79,0:19:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Usopp!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.04,0:19:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Guys!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.67,0:19:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't move! One move, and this guy is dead!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:58.17,0:20:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They already had a landing \Nparty hiding here, did they?!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.01,0:20:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done, Corporal!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:04.80,0:20:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Guys, hurry and let them know!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.14,0:20:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. \NIf they leave now, they won't make it in time.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.52,0:20:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But what else can we do?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:11.39,0:20:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, the straw-hatted \Nlad and the others will be...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.73,0:20:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a mess.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:17.18,0:20:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.19,0:20:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Gramps, you're a pirate, right? Do something.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.11,0:20:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's crazy! \NMaybe I am a pirate, but this ship is my coffin.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:26.91,0:20:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up in the mountains, \Nand no matter what I do...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.45,0:20:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So we just have to bring it down, don't we?{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.54,0:20:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The wind that blows down from the mountains...!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.33,0:20:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to set sail!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:39.67,0:20:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you standing around for?! \NMen, remove the chock planks!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:43.38,0:20:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.47,0:20:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop your weapons, or else!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.23,0:20:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,– Usopp! \N– Damn it!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.65,0:20:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Guys! Hurry and get out of here!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:56.27,0:20:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They're planning to finish us \Nall off, one way or another!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:59.32,0:21:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep your mouth shut!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.33,0:21:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you, cowards!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:03.24,0:21:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't even have to wait for the captain to land,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:05.36,0:21:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it's all over now. Corporal!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:09.87,0:21:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure enough...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:11.50,0:21:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You cowards!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:12.75,0:21:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I can handle bullets just fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:14.54,0:21:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But we {\i1}can't{\i0} handle them!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:18.42,0:21:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take the treasure of Zenny,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.13,0:21:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,along with the heads of the Straw Hat pirates!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.71,0:21:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time to send you to hell!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.60,0:21:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Sail on!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:36.31,0:21:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I-Impossible! \NA pirate ship, coming out of the mountains?!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:39.82,0:21:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Attack of the Zenny Pirates!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.44,0:21:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Old man!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:52.20,0:21:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,How's tricks?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:10.86,0:23:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, nice going! I've gotta give him more credit!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:13.16,0:23:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,– Is this any time for admiration?! \N– Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:15.70,0:23:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a good idea to show yourself, \Nwhen you're the one they're after!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:18.04,0:23:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Gramps, let me take care of the treasure!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:21.08,0:23:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Naughty girl...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:22.17,0:23:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If something is dear to you, \Nfight to protect it, old man!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:25.59,0:23:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, on One Piece:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:27.09,0:23:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Whereabouts of the Island Treasure! \NAttack of the Zenny Pirates!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:30.76,0:23:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna be the Pirate King!!
